      },
      "date": "2013-03-13 23:12:44.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nI'm not super thrilled with this, since normally it is better to have the tunable named the same as the variable, and also internally there is still a lot of other variables named \"dirty\" and only this one value using \"pinned\".  In some regard we could stick with the \"dirty\" name and just describe that pages are still counted against max_dirty_mb until their write has committed.\n\nThat said, I'm not strongly _against_ this change and am willing to accept it if you & others think this is an improvement.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
