        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-04-11 10:53:04.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nUnfortunately, patch must be rebased to catch recent test fixes in order to pass.\n\nPersonally, I'm fine to define \"dirty pages\" to mean \"unwritten + unstable\", and drop this patch entirely, since I don't think renaming the /proc file will instead break user tunables for very marginal benefits.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "b4b21a0d0481c088e085fb5d06fbdb7f48c322f8",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 124,
        "name": "Prakash Surya",
        "email": "lists@prakashsurya.com",
        "username": "prakash"
      },
      "date": "2013-04-11 16:52:39.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nOK. I'll go ahead and drop this patch entirely, in favor of \"dirty\" meaning \"dirty + unstable\". I believe this is consistent with the way the per OSC cl_dirty_mb value is used too.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
