        "committer": {
          "name": "Prakash Surya",
          "email": "surya1@llnl.gov",
          "date": "2013-04-02 20:33:40.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "subject": "LU-2139 obdclass: Rename max_dirty_pages variable",
        "message": "LU-2139 obdclass: Rename max_dirty_pages variable\n\nThis patch renames the \"max_dirty_pages\" global variable to\n\"max_pinned_pages\". This is in anticipation for tracking the number of\noutstanding unstable pages on the system, and limiting the sum of the\noutstanding dirty and unstable pages by this value. Thus, the previous\nname doesn't fit since it will be used to limit both dirty and unstable\npages. The mnemonic being both dirty and unstable pages are \"pinned\" in\nmemory, so this is the maximum number of lustre pages pinned in memory\nat any point in time.\n\nAs a result of the change described above, the file serving as the\ninterface to setting and getting this value was change as well.\nPreviously it was named \"max_dirty_mb\", now it is named \"max_pinned_mb\".\n\nSigned-off-by: Prakash Surya <surya1@llnl.gov>\nChange-Id: Ibed3865a80ef153855e9ca4b570837ac24a4df23\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
